ce:section.ce:para:
Since much attention has been devoted to the Zn compounds for solar cells [86-89], we first evaluate the absorption spectra of the ZnP-C60-oligo-PPEs system against the experiment. Our theoretical result shows the absorption wavelength, λabs, of 440.10 nm (see Fig. 2
                        ), which agrees well with the experimental value [79] (λmax = 440 nm). We have also compared the result of the ZINDO/S method with the TDDFT/B3PW91 level of theory for the free porphyrin, C60 fullerene, and Oligo-PPEs molecules (Fig. 3
                         a-f). The results demonstrate that ZINDO/S reproduces both Q (550–750 nm) and potent Soret (400–500 nm) bands for porphyrin molecule in agreement with the TDDFT/ B3PW91 finding and also other reported results at the TD-B3LYP/6-31G level of theory [90]. In addition, the obtained λmax value (350 nm) for the C60 fullerene is inconsistent with the observed one in the experiment [91]. As can be seen in Fig. 3 (e-f), in the case of Oligo-PPEs, we observed UV–Vis spectra in the range of 200–400 nm in both ZINDO/S and B3PW91 functionals, which are in good agreement with experimental results [92].
